Layout mirrors upstream include/: the per-component headers live in
walnuts/, with walnuts.hpp the umbrella that includes them all.

Integration reference: bairrtt (inst/include/{walnuts,walnuts.hpp,
WALNUTS_LICENSE}). These headers were pulled FRESH from upstream, not
copied from bairrtt.

API drift vs the bairrtt-era snapshot (re-verified at C1):
  - The AdaptiveWalnuts -> freeze (sampler()) -> WalnutsSampler
    lifecycle, the diagonal MassEstimator, and the
    InitChainConfig(step_size, position, mass) ctor are UNCHANGED.
  - WarmupConfig gained a step-size convergence tolerance
    (step_size_converge_tol_, from upstream's "init-stepsize" work);
    api.hpp's internal detail::sample() signature was refactored to take
    the SamplingConfig directly. Neither touches the per-chain path this
    package uses; both are C2 concerns (WarmupConfig sizing), not C1.
  - Diagnostics: the ChainHandler concept (concepts.hpp) still surfaces
    only position / lp / step_size / diag_inv_mass; GlobalHandler adds
    on_r_hat. There are NO treedepth, divergent, n_leapfrog, or energy
    hooks, confirming the plan's Q(c) claim against fresh upstream.
